<br>
The &quot;Arcane Masters&quot; guild set up a race from Akanon to the library in Erudin.<br>
<br>
Rules of the race are as follows.<br>
<br>
a server was picked random and the guild leader was able to get a GM to grant him an extention of the guild on that server, for communication purposes.<br>
<br>
1) Level 1 gnomes of any class. Level 2 gnomes are not be allowed (but at the end of the race there were a couple who got their levels fighting stuff on the way)<br>
<br>
2) NO TELEPORTS OF ANY KIND ARE ALLOWED. SoW and Buffs were allowed if you spend the time to beg for one. BUT you cant beg over /ooc, /auction or /shout. The same rules apply to being bound to a city.<br>
<br>
3) The race will consist of 3 separate races. Akanon to BB docks, Freeport to Qeynos docks, and the final leg from Erudin docks to the library in Erudin. Mostly because the boats end up being the balancing or unbalancing factor, especially if you just barely miss one.<br>
<br>
4) You chose your route. As long as you do not get teleported, you can get to Erudin which ever direction you choose. Some may choose thru NRo/Oasis/SRo/Feerrott/Rathe Mtns/Lake Rathe/SKarana/Nkarana, others may choose Commons/Kithicor/HHPass/EKarana/Nkarana and some may choose Commons/Kithicor/Rivervale/Misty/Runnyeye/Beholder/EKarana/NKarana<br>
<br>
The first gnome to make it to the library was named the winner. Anyone who decided that they were out of the race because they died too often and felt like making an erudite to watch the end of the race were allowed to do so. There would be an officer in Erudin to invite you in to the guild for communication purposes.<br>
<br>
This race took about 3 hours to run and of the 25 gnomes who started, most of  them actually finished.<br>
<br>
It was a blast to invade places like Kithicor with 20+ level 1 gnomes.<br>
<br>
<br>
